<TITLE> DB officials sued for threatening 'crossfire' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has ordered judicial investigation into charges of extortion and attempted murder against four, including two Detective Branch (DB) officials. Chief metropolitan magistrate Shahadat Hossain gave the order on Monday. A businessman of Shabujbag, Zahirul Haque filed the case with Dhaka's Chief Metropolitan Magistrates' Court. The accused DB officials are assistant commissioner Matiur Rahman and inspector Md Kibria. The case's first information report states that on May 18, the accused officials picked Zahirul up in a vehicle from his dairy farm in front of his residence and took him to Motijheel AGB colony. The abductors demanded Tk 20 lakh from him and threatened to killing him in 'crossfire' if he did not comply. They managed to extort Tk 1 lakh later. Shabujbag police refused to accept the FIR of the case after they were informed. bdne
